# Issues and Resolutions

## VMware Virtualization Environment

### Issue:
Certain Windows security features were not supported within the virtual machine environment.

### Investigation:
Reviewed Windows Security settings and verified virtualization configuration.

### Resolution:
Documented the limitation and continued testing with supported security controls.

---

## Windows Update Restart Requirement

### Issue:
Windows Update required a system restart before confirming the device was fully updated.

### Resolution:
Restarted the virtual machine and verified the system reported that it was up to date.

---

## File Permission Testing

### Issue:
Initial folder permissions allowed the standard user account (labuser) to access the protected folder.

### Investigation:
Reviewed NTFS permissions and identified inherited permissions as the cause.

### Resolution:
Disabled inheritance and configured administrator-only permissions to demonstrate access control and least privilege.

---

## User Permission Testing

### Issue:
Testing administrator functions with the standard user account required credential elevation.

### Investigation:
Verified differences between administrator and standard user privileges.

### Resolution:
Confirmed that labuser operated with standard permissions while labadmin1 maintained administrative access
